caves,
so
that
if
you
enter
Blue
John
Gap
you
would
do
well
to
mark
your
steps
and
to
have
a
good
store
of
candles,
or
you
may
never
make
your
way
back
to
the
daylight
again.
I
have
not
yet
gone
deeply
into
it,
but
this
very
day
I
stood
at
the
mouth
of
the
arched
tunnel,
and
peering
down
into
the
black
recesses
beyond,
I
vowed
that
when
my
health
returned
I
would
devote
some
