to
exploring
those
mysterious
depths
and
finding
out
for
myself
how
far
the
Roman
had
penetrated
into
the
Derbyshire
hills.
Strange
how
superstitious
these
countrymen
are!
I
should
have
thought
better
of
young
Armitage,
for
he
is
a
man
of
some
education
and
