life.
I
was
standing
at
the
Blue
John
Gap
when
he
came
across
the
field
to
me.
"Well,
doctor,"
said
he,
"you're
not
afraid,
anyhow."
"Afraid!"
I
answered.
"Afraid
of
what?"
"Of
it,"
said
he,
with
