would
naturally
choose
for
his
work.
On
one
occasion
a
gap
had
been
made
in
a
wall,
and
some
of
the
stones
scattered
for
a
considerable
distance.
Human
agency
again,
in
my
opinion.
Finally,
Armitage
clinched
all
his
arguments
by
telling
me
that
he
had
actually
heard
the
Creature
indeed,
that
anyone
could
hear
it
who
remained
long
enough
at
the
Gap.
It
was
a
distant
roaring
of
an
immense
volume.
I
could
not
but
smile
at
this,
knowing,
as
I
do,
the
strange
